SUMMARY:Deadline: Innovate UK: Next Wave Breakthrough Wave 1\, Createch (20
 26)
DESCRIPTION:Next Wave Breakthrough Wave 1 is Innovate UK's current open Cre
 atech competition\, investing up to GBP 10 million in early-stage innovati
 on at the intersection of creative technology and the frontier industries 
 named in the Industrial Strategy: video games\, advertising and marketing\
 , film and television\, and music and the performing and visual arts. It f
 unds industrial research to take innovations beyond proof of concept and d
 e-risk future investment\, with individual projects between GBP 100\,000 a
 nd 500\,000 in total costs. Grant rates depend on organisation size\, from
  70 percent for micro and small enterprises down to 50 percent for large o
 rganisations\, so applicants must supply match funding for the remainder. 
 The lead must be a UK-registered SME\; non-profits and CICs are barred fro
 m leading\, though they can participate as collaborators alongside a comme
 rcial lead. Non-funded partners may be based internationally. The competit
 ion opened 23 June 2026 and closes 11 August 2026 at 11:00am UK time. NOTE
  ON FIT: this is an R&D competition for creative-technology product develo
 pment\, not a fund for delivering festivals or exhibitions\, so it suits a
 n organisation whose work can be framed as industrial research with a comm
 ercial SME lead.\n\nOrganisation: Innovate UK\, UK Research and Innovation
 \nLocation: United Kingdom. Project work must be carried out in the UK\, r
 esults exploited in the UK\, and most funding spent in the UK.\nAward: GBP
  100\,000 to 500\,000 total project costs from a GBP 10 million fund\; no 
 organisation may receive more than GBP 3 million across the programme. Gra
 nt intervention rates for industrial research: up to 70 percent for micro 
 and small enterprises\, 60 percent for medium\, 50 percent for large. Rese
 arch organisations doing non-economic work can claim up to 100 percent\, o
 r 80 percent of full economic cost for academic institutions. The balance 
 is match funding. No application fee.\nDuration: 9 to 12 months\; projects
  must start by 1 January 2027 and end by 31 December 2027.\n\nMore: https:
 //apply-for-innovation-funding.service.gov.uk/competition/2517/overview/6f
 f2066d-4639-44e6-bb4f-ce7099222739?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&u
 tm_medium=referral
URL:https://apply-for-innovation-funding.service.gov.uk/competition/2517/ov
 erview/6ff2066d-4639-44e6-bb4f-ce7099222739?utm_source=artificialnouveaugr
 antdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:United Kingdom. Project work must be carried out in the UK\, resul
 ts exploited in the UK\, and most funding spent in the UK.
